How to Publish Your App on the Apple App Store and Google Play Store

1. Apple App Store (iOS)
------------------------
A. Create an Apple Developer Account
- Go to: https://developer.apple.com/programs/
- Click Enroll and follow the steps.
- You’ll need: An Apple ID, legal name, address, phone number, $99/year fee (individual or company)

B. Prepare Your App for Submission
- Build your app for release (`flutter build ios --release`)
- Open the project in Xcode (`open ios/Runner.xcworkspace`)
- Set your app’s version, build number, and bundle identifier in Xcode
- Set up app icons, launch images, and permissions

C. Upload Your App
- In Xcode, select “Any iOS Device” and go to Product > Archive
- After archiving, click “Distribute App” and follow the prompts to upload to App Store Connect

D. Fill Out App Store Connect Info
- Go to https://appstoreconnect.apple.com/
- Create a new app record
- Fill out metadata, screenshots, pricing, etc.
- Submit your app for review

2. Google Play Store (Android)
-----------------------------
A. Create a Google Play Developer Account
- Go to: https://play.google.com/console/about/
- Click Get Started
- Sign in with your Google account
- Pay the one-time $25 registration fee
- Fill out your developer profile

B. Prepare Your App for Submission
- Build your app for release (`flutter build apk --release`)
- Sign your APK or AAB (Android App Bundle) (see: https://docs.flutter.dev/deployment/android#signing-the-app)
- Prepare app icons, screenshots, and a privacy policy if needed

C. Upload Your App
- In the Play Console, click “Create app”
- Fill out app details, upload your APK/AAB, and provide required assets
- Fill out content rating, target audience, and privacy policy
- Submit for review

Summary Table
-------------
| Platform | Account Cost | Link to Register | Review Time      |
|----------|--------------|------------------|------------------|
| iOS      | $99/year     | https://developer.apple.com/programs/ | 1-3 days (can be longer) |
| Android  | $25 one-time | https://play.google.com/console/about/ | Hours to a few days      |

Tips
----
- Both stores require privacy policies and app screenshots.
- Your app must comply with their guidelines (no malware, no copyright violations, etc.).
- You can test your app on real devices before publishing.

If you want, I can walk you through the process for either store step-by-step, or help you prepare your app for submission! 